result.execSummary:
The defendant Desiree Marie Caldwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
1) The defendant must provide DNA; the analysis may be expunged upon application to the Department of Justice. 
2) The DNA surcharge was paid in full prior to disposition.
3) The court waived all other court costs in this matter.

2:40 PM Prosecuting attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Desiree Marie Caldwell appeared by video.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for Desiree Marie Caldwell.  Def waives all in-person hearing KIV.  Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Agreement is recited by Court- def pleading to simple possession of THC; joint rec for court costs.  State moves to amend Count 1 to misdemeanor possession of THC; granted by Court.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Def's constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for plea.  Def enters a plea of Guilty.  Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds defendant guilty of amended Count 1 and orders a JOC; Count 2 is DRI.  DA asks Court to accept agreement.  Defense attorney asks Court to accept agreement.  Def declines to make a statement to the Court. 
Court orders:
$200 DNA surcharge only (was prepaid).
Appeal rights provided.  Fingerprints and DNA to be provided to the Sheriff.
